Recent changes to JIRA now cause notification to appear on the side in a mini text box instead of on the top part of the page (re-index notification for example). The recent changes while looks better; is a bit intrusive in it's placement (as it sometimes blocks user from navigating around the instance). 

While I do understand that most of these notifications are important; sometimes the user is not done with the changes yet (thus not doing what that is being suggested in the notification for a short period of time).It will be great if there is a check box on the notification box to allow user to temporarily disable the notification from appearing so that they can proceed with their daily operations.

