When doing a doing a search for issues, if you filter by *Fix Version*, an error displays {color:red}"Error occurred communicating with the server. Please reload the page and try again."{color}

This only displays for users not logged in trying to filter through issues by *Fix Version*. This error does not display for users already logged in. As a user not logged in, I'm able to view all issues but I'm not able to filter by *Fix Version*. (Project Permissions for *Browse Projects* is set to Anyone (Users) so that anyone can view the issues in the first place)

h3. Steps to Reproduce:
I've replicated this error message on my own instance. I created *Fix Versions* and added them to some issues. I changed the Project Permissions to allow anyone to view the issues. Then I logged out and viewed the issues. From there I tried to filter by *Fix Versions* and received the error {color: red}"Error occurred communicating with the server. Please reload the page and try again."{color}


 What I receive in Javascript Console for my instance. 
{noformat}
POST https://instance.jira-dev.com/rest/issueNav/1/issueTable 500 (Internal Server Error)
{noformat}

if I try hitting the url I receive a 500 error.

