Using Tempo Timesheets to create worklog the updateAuthor is wrong when other user writes worklog.

Use case: 
If User1(Developer) creates worklog and User2(Scrum master) edits his worklog the updateAuthor will be User1 but should be User2.

If User2(Scrum master) create worklog for User1(Developer) the author
and updateAuthor will be User1 but updateAuthor should be User2.

When we are creating worklog we use this JiraServiceContext implementation like this.
{code}
new JiraServiceContextImpl(user, new SimpleErrorCollection(), jiraAuthenticationContext.getI18nHelper());
{code}

Where the "user" variable is the person that owns the worklog (in my use case the user1) so when 
{code}
WorklogResult validateCreate(JiraServiceContext jiraServiceContext, WorklogInputParameters params) 
{code} in DefaultWorklogService.java is called the getLoggedInApplicationUser() returns not the loggedInUser but the user send into JiraServiceContex therefore the wrong UpdateAuthor.

